ASSEMBLY CONCURRENT RESOLUTION—Directing the Joint
Interim Standing Committee on the Judiciary to conduct a
study relating to road safety.
1 RESOLVED BY THE ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, THE
2 SENATE CONCURRING, That the Joint Interim Standing Committee
3 on the Judiciary is hereby directed to conduct a study during the
4 2025-2026 legislative interim relating to road safety; and be it
5 further
6 RESOLVED, That the study must include, without limitation:
7 1. A review of the laws of this State concerning the operation
8 of electric bicycles and electric scooters and whether additional
9 regulation of electric bicycles and electric scooters is necessary to
10 promote public safety;
11 2. An examination of data and other information concerning
12 traffic violations committed in school zones and an analysis of
13 whether increasing the penalties associated with traffic violations
14 committed in school zones would promote public safety; and
15 3. An evaluation of the power of local governments, including,
16 without limitation, school districts, to regulate electric bicycles and
17 electric scooters in their respective jurisdictions and to regulate
18 traffic violations committed in school zones, and whether additional
19 powers related to these topics should be afforded to local
20 governments, including, without limitation, school districts; and be
21 it further
22 RESOLVED, That any recommended legislation proposed by the
23 Committee must be approved by a majority of the members of the
-
